ConocoPhillips (NYSE:COP) Position Cut by Alpha Cubed Investments LLC

Bartolome Carpio |
Miércoles, Julio 19, 2017







ConocoPhillips (COP): What's the Story?
Alpha Windward LLC boosted its position in shares of ConocoPhillips by 0.9% in the first quarter. Good Life Advisors LLC purchased a new stake in shares of ConocoPhillips during the fourth quarter worth approximately $693,000. Financial Management Professionals Inc. now owns 2,288 shares of the energy producer's stock valued at $114,000 after buying an additional 6 shares during the period. Financial Management Professionals Inc. raised its stake in ConocoPhillips by 0.3% in the first quarter. First Eagle Investment Management LLC now owns 10,065,496 shares of the energy producer's stock worth $501,966,000 after buying an additional 1,744,860 shares in the last quarter.Natixis Asset Management decreased Axis Capital Holdings Ltd (NYSE:AXS) stake by 37,380 shares to 32,960 valued at $2.15 million in 2016Q4.
Rhumbline Advisers increased Conocophillips Com (COP) stake by 4.23% reported in 2016Q4 SEC filing. Quadrant Capital Group LLC now owns 2,413 shares of the energy producer's stock worth $109,000 after buying an additional 569 shares during the last quarter. Finally, Crestwood Advisors Group LLC purchased a new stake in shares of ConocoPhillips during the first quarter valued at approximately $131,000. FMR LLC now owns 61,497,903 shares of the energy producer's stock worth $3,066,900,000 after buying an additional 3,982,002 shares during the period. Perhaps, that suggests something about why 64.19% of the outstanding share supply is held by institutional investors. ConocoPhillips (COP) shares have been seen trading -18.77% off its 52 week- peak value and changed 11.31% from its 52 week-bottom price value. 407,195 shares of the stock traded hands. The firm's 50 day moving average price is $45.46 and its 200 day moving average price is $47.90. The company has market cap of $15.87 million.ConocoPhillips (NYSE:COP) last released its earnings results on Tuesday, May 2nd. First Natl reported 33,010 shares or 0.23% of all its holdings. The firm had revenue of $7.77 billion during the quarter, compared to the consensus estimate of $7.47 billion. ConocoPhillips had a negative net margin of 5.05% and a negative return on equity of 5.92%. During the same period in the previous year, the company posted ($0.95) earnings per share. Equities research analysts predict that ConocoPhillips will post $0.26 earnings per share for the current year.ConocoPhillips also recently announced a dividend for shareholders that was paid on Thursday June 1st, 2017. Investors of record on Monday, July 24th will be given a dividend of $0.265 per share. The dividend yield was $2.44. The rating was downgraded by Bernstein on Thursday, July 6 to "Market Perform". ConocoPhillips's dividend payout ratio (DPR) is presently -95.50%.ConocoPhillips declared that its Board of Directors has authorized a stock buyback program on Wednesday, March 29th that allows the company to buyback $3.00 billion in shares. This repurchase authorization authorizes the energy producer to repurchase up to 5.3% of its stock through open market purchases. Stock buyback programs are usually an indication that the company's leadership believes its shares are undervalued. If you are accessing this news story on another publication, it was illegally copied and reposted in violation of worldwide trademark & copyright laws. The correct version of this news story can be read at https://www.baseball-news-blog.com/2017/07/18/intrust-bank-na-cuts-position-in-conocophillips-cop-updated.html.In recent action, ConocoPhillips (COP) has made a move of -4.27% over the past month, which has come on weak relative transaction volume. Cowen and Company reiterated an "outperform" rating and set a $59.00 price objective on shares of ConocoPhillips in a report on Thursday, March 30th. Instinet reissued a "neutral" rating and issued a $54.00 target price on shares of ConocoPhillips in a research report on Monday, April 3rd. Royal Bank Of Canada set a $62.00 price objective on ConocoPhillips and gave the stock a "buy" rating in a report on Sunday. The stock of ConocoPhillips (NYSE:COP) has "Buy" rating given on Friday, April 7 by Scotia Capital. The stock has a consensus rating of "Hold" and a consensus target price of $55.77. Four investment analysts have rated the stock with a sell rating, nine have issued a hold rating, fifteen have assigned a buy rating and one has issued a strong buy rating to the stock. The company has a consensus rating of "Hold" and an average price target of $55.77. Shares for $431,590 were sold by McMorran James D. The sale was disclosed in a filing with the Securities & Exchange Commission, which is available through this hyperlink. Closely-held shares are those owned by insiders, major shareholders and employees, while restricted stock refers to insider shares that can not be traded because of a temporary restriction such as the lock-up period after an initial public offering.




