Axis Capital Holdings Limited (NYSE:AXS) Downgraded to “Hold” at Zacks Investment Research

					Posted by Danessa Lincoln on Jul 18th, 2017 // No Comments 




Zacks Investment Research downgraded shares of Axis Capital Holdings Limited (NYSE:AXS) from a buy rating to a hold rating in a research report sent to investors on Wednesday morning. 
According to Zacks, “AXIS Capital continues to build on its Specialty Insurance, Reinsurance, and Accident and Health to pave way for long-term growth. It remains focused on deploying resources prudently, enhancing efficiencies and better serving clients and brokers across the globe. It has also been improving its portfolio mix and underwriting profitability apart from strengthening the casualty and professional lines in the insurance segment. However, stiff competition in the reinsurance industry slowing growth and lowering profitability along with escalating expenses eating into margins remain concerns. Also, shares of AXIS Capital have underperformed the Zacks categorized Property and Casualty industry year to date. Yet, the company has been witnessing estimates moving north over the last 60 days. The company is set to report second results on Jul 26. However, Zacks Rank #3 when combined with Earnings ESP of -6.98% makes prediction difficult for beat or miss.”


 Get Axis Capital Holdings Limited alerts:



AXS has been the topic of several other reports. Deutsche Bank AG  reiterated a hold rating and issued a $64.00 target price (down from $66.00) on shares of Axis Capital Holdings Limited in a report on Wednesday, March 15th. ValuEngine upgraded Axis Capital Holdings Limited from a hold rating to a buy rating in a report on Friday, June 2nd. Citigroup Inc. upped their target price on Axis Capital Holdings Limited from $60.00 to $61.00 and gave the company a sell rating in a report on Friday, April 7th. BidaskClub cut Axis Capital Holdings Limited from a sell rating to a strong sell rating in a report on Saturday, June 24th. Finally, Keefe, Bruyette & Woods  reiterated a hold rating and issued a $64.00 target price on shares of Axis Capital Holdings Limited in a report on Friday, June 2nd. Six investment analysts have rated the stock with a sell rating, five have assigned  a hold rating and two have given a buy rating to the company’s stock. The company  has an average rating of Hold and a consensus target price of $66.78.




Axis Capital Holdings Limited (NYSE:AXS) opened at 63.74 on Wednesday. The firm’s 50-day moving average is $64.49 and its 200-day moving average is $66.02. Axis Capital Holdings Limited has a 52-week low of $52.67 and a 52-week high of $71.06. The firm has a market capitalization of $5.39 billion, a P/E ratio of 13.23 and a beta of 0.60. 
Axis Capital Holdings Limited (NYSE:AXS) last released its quarterly earnings results on Wednesday, April 26th. The insurance provider reported $0.59 earnings per share for the quarter, missing the Thomson Reuters’ consensus estimate of $0.81 by $0.22. The firm had revenue of $1.51 billion for the quarter, compared to the consensus estimate of $1.69 billion. Axis Capital Holdings Limited had a return on equity of 7.86% and a net margin of 11.74%. The business’s revenue for the quarter was down 10.5% on a year-over-year basis. During the same quarter last year, the firm posted $1.07 earnings per share.  On average, equities analysts expect that  Axis Capital Holdings Limited will post $3.93 earnings per share for the current year. 
COPYRIGHT VIOLATION WARNING: “Axis Capital Holdings Limited (NYSE:AXS) Downgraded to “Hold” at Zacks Investment Research” was  reported by Markets Daily and is the property of of Markets Daily. If you are accessing this article on another publication, it was copied illegally and republished in violation of US and international copyright and trademark legislation. The legal version of this article can be viewed at https://www.themarketsdaily.com/2017/07/18/axis-capital-holdings-limited-nyseaxs-downgraded-to-hold-at-zacks-investment-research.html. 
The firm also recently declared a quarterly dividend, which was paid on Monday, July 17th. Shareholders of record on Friday, June 30th were paid a $0.38 dividend. This represents a $1.52 annualized dividend and a yield of 2.38%. The ex-dividend date  was Wednesday, June 28th. Axis Capital Holdings Limited’s dividend payout ratio (DPR) is presently 31.73%. 
A number of institutional investors have recently modified their holdings of the stock. Comerica Bank raised its position in shares of  Axis Capital Holdings Limited by 54.0% in the fourth quarter. Comerica Bank now owns 9,933 shares of the insurance provider’s stock valued at $649,000 after buying an additional 3,482 shares during the period.  Envestnet Asset Management Inc. raised its position in shares of  Axis Capital Holdings Limited by 555.0% in the fourth quarter. Envestnet Asset Management Inc. now owns 10,703 shares of the insurance provider’s stock valued at $698,000 after buying an additional 9,069 shares during the period.  Tudor Investment Corp Et Al acquired a new position in shares of  Axis Capital Holdings Limited during the fourth quarter valued at about $389,000.  Teachers Advisors LLC raised its position in shares of  Axis Capital Holdings Limited by 14.7% in the fourth quarter. Teachers Advisors LLC now owns 121,576 shares of the insurance provider’s stock valued at $7,935,000 after buying an additional 15,588 shares during the period.  Finally, Macquarie Group Ltd. raised its position in shares of  Axis Capital Holdings Limited by 31.8% in the fourth quarter. Macquarie Group Ltd. now owns 2,900 shares of the insurance provider’s stock valued at $189,000 after buying an additional 700 shares during the period. 88.27% of the stock is currently owned by hedge funds and other institutional investors. 
About Axis Capital Holdings Limited
AXIS Capital Holdings Limited is a holding company. The Company provides a range of specialty (re)insurance, through subsidiaries and branch networks- based in Bermuda, the United States, Canada, Europe and Singapore. Its business consists of two global underwriting platforms: AXIS Insurance and AXIS Re.
