Axis Capital Holdings Limited (AXS) Holdings Decreased by APG Asset Management N.V. - Highlight Press

























































Highlight PressBreaking Tech News, Entertainment, Mortgages and More
Axis Capital Holdings Limited (AXS) Holdings Decreased by APG Asset Management N.V.
July 21, 2017 By Clarence Martin Tweet        Advertisement





Axis Capital Holdings Limited (NYSE:AXS). 
 APG Asset Management N.V. says it decreased its stake in Axis Capital Holdings Limited stock by 34,500 shares in its quarterly SEC filing.  Its investment stood at $82,825,000 a decrease of $5,348,000 as of the end of the quarter. 
 These firms have also modified their investment in AXS.   As of quarter end Assenagon Asset Management S.a. had acquired 21,210 shares growing its holdings by 24.1%. The value in dollars increased from $5,894,000 to $7,057,000 a change of $1,163,000 quarter over quarter. Aperio Group, LLC added to its investment by buying 361 shares an increase of 8.2% as of 06/30/2017. Aperio Group, LLC currently owns 4,757 shares with a value of $308,000. The value of the position overall is up by 4.4%.
 Ls Investment Advisors, LLC bolstered its position by buying 318 shares an increase of 6.3%. Ls Investment Advisors, LLC owns 5,363 shares worth $347,000. The total value of its holdings increased 2.7%.
  On December 2 the company was rated “Neutral” in a report from Macquarie which was a cut from the previous “Outperform” rating. On November 22, 2016 Citigroup added AXS to its research portfolio with an initial rating of “Sell”.





 On November 15, 2016 the stock rating was changed to a “Sell” by Goldman Sachs which is down from the previous “Sell” rating. On May 26 the stock rating was downgraded from “Buy” to “Neutral” in a report issued by Janney Capital.
 UBS both downgraded the stock and lowered the price target on February 16 changing the price target from $59.00 to $54.00 and setting the rating at “Neutral” which had previously been “Buy”. On February 16 the company was downgraded to “Neutral” from “Buy” with a current price target of $54.00 in an announcement from UBS.
 The company is now down since yesterday’s close of $64.72.  The company also recently declared a dividend paid on Monday July 17th, 2017.  The dividend was $0.380 per share for the quarter which is $1.52 annualized.  This dividend amount represented a yeild of $2.38.  The ex-dividend date was Wednesday the 28th of June 2017. 
 It is trading at $64.60 a tad below the 50 day moving average of $64.67 and a bit lower than the 200 day moving average of $65.94.  The 50 day moving average was down $-0.20 or -0.32% and the 200 day average went down $-1.47 or -2.23%. 
 Axis Capital Holdings Limited currently has a P/E ratio of 13.38 and market cap is 5.45B.  In the latest earnings report the EPS was $4.82 and is expected to be $3.93 for the current year with 84,579,000 shares currently outstanding.  Next quarter’s EPS is forecasted at $0.89 and the next full year EPS is projected to be $4.85. 






