AXIS Capital Holdings Limited Key Developments

Axis Capital Holdings Ltd. Announces Executive Appointments
Jul 7 17
Axis Capital Holdings Ltd. announced that it is acquiring Novae Group plc. Axis Capital also announced that, following the completion of the transaction, Novae CEO Matthew Fosh will be appointed the company's executive chair, Europe. Among his responsibilities in his new role, Fosh will help guide the integration of the two businesses. Additionally, Novae CUO Robert Forster will have a senior underwriting management role on a leadership team of Axis' international insurance division, which is led by CEO Mark Gregory.


AXIS Capital Holdings Limited, Novae Group Plc - M&A Call
Jul 5 17
To discuss AXIS Capital Holdings Limited Acquisition of Novae Group plc


Axis Insurance Announces Management Changes
Jun 28 17
Axis Insurance announced that it has named a head for its Excess & Surplus Lines P/C Insurers Property. Marc Nance was named as executive vice president. Nance is to be based in Chicago and will be responsible for managing and expanding the firm's E&S property business in the US. He is to take the place of Chris Endsley, who recently retired.


